<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4956301>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. SEM of Syllophopsis peetersi sp. nov. (worker), Head. (a) full face-view; (b) lateral-view, eye (E); (c) eyes with 9-ommatidia; (d) curved sensilla in-between eye ommatidia; (e) median clypeus with two teeth, anteromedian seta (MCS), anterior tentorial pit (at), frontal carina (Frc), clypeus (Clp), mandible (Md); (f–g) sculptured mandibles with 4-teeth and one denticle on second basal tooth; (h) anterior tentorial pit, enlarged; (i) antennal basal socket, torulus (to), torular lobe (tol); (j–k) enlarged basal socket with antennal bulbus having series of sensilla trichodea; (l–m) enlarged sensilla trichodea and its basal socket." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4956301/files/figure.png" .

